ENTRY       EC 3.4.21.5                 Enzyme
NAME        thrombin;
            fibrinogenase;
            thrombase;
            thrombofort;
            topical;
            thrombin-C;
            tropostasin;
            activated blood-coagulation factor II;
            blood-coagulation factor IIa;
            factor IIa;
            E thrombin;
            beta-thrombin;
            gamma-thrombin
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Serine endopeptidases
REACTION    Selective cleavage of Arg!Gly bonds in fibrinogen to form fibrin and release fibrinopeptides A and B
COMMENT     Formed from prothrombin. More selective than trypsin and plasmin. In peptidase family S1 (trypsin family).
HISTORY     EC 3.4.21.5 created 1961 as EC 3.4.4.13, transferred 1972 to EC 3.4.21.5
